      "raw_text": "DAYTON, Wash, June TO-\nWhile rains are needed badly to adj\nvance the growing crop in this sec\nton, farmers are hopeful. The pic\nneer grain growers of Dayton paral-\nlie; this season with that of 1897,\nwhen rains did not come until the\nthird week of June. T. S. Leonard,\na pioneer what grower of Columbia\ncounty. said the backward condition\nof grain now does not indicate a\ncrop failure."
